examples.en: I scraped my knee when I fell.
The cat scraped at the armchair.
The car scraped against the curb.
Tom scraped down all four walls in the room.
She scraped the foam off her coffee.
He scraped out a tune at a cello.
Labour scraped in by a small majority.
Someone had scraped the car with a key.
I scraped the lichen from the tombstone.
The deer scraped its antlers against the tree.
The earth was scraped away to uncover a trap door.
She scraped her fingernails across the blackboard.
She had scraped together enough money for college.
The coat was too long; the hem scraped the pavement.
Her mother always bandages her scraped knees very carefully.
The train was crowded, but I scraped in just before the door closed.
I scraped along until my next cheque arrived, by borrowing from my relations.
